Check model versions! The Overfitted one may be better for your usecase!


Description:

The funny small lady.


This LORA isn't perfect due to the small amount of good data on Maho, it was trained on only 25 images, mostly from the front, and mostly in her signature outfit.

items.name: Narita Brian (umamusume)
items.description:
LoRA of Narita Brian (umamusume)

All of my works is free. If you'd like to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee. 👍

Recommend options

  • LoRA weight 0.7~

  • Trigger words

    • base

      • narita brian \(umamusume\)

    • Racing competition clothes :

      • midriff, fingerless gloves, coat on shoulders, plaid skirt, belt, asymmetrical footwear, cleavage, single thighhigh, chest sarashi

    • Casual clothes :

      • long sleeves, white shirt, purple pants

    • Blaze costume NOT included.

  • Use animefull based model

  • Settings

    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • about 20 steps, CFG scale 3.5~6.5

    • kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

    • If using highres

      • Latent series

      • Denoising strength 0.50~0.65

LoRA training info

  • based on Animefull-pruned

  • 68 images of narita brian

    • 4x low quality 29 images

    • 8x medium quality 17 images

    • 16x high quality 30 images

    • => 1 epoch = 812 images

  • replaced character feature tags with narita brian \(umamusume\)

    • horse girl, horse tail, brown hair, yellow eyes, etc.

  • using aspect ratio bucketing

  • resolution : 768x768

  • rank=alpha=16

  • using dadaptation

  • batch size = 4, 9 epochs trained

  • clip skip = 1

This LoRA may be compatible with animefull-based models (ex. AbyssOrangeMix Series...)

All uploaded images are generated by AOM3A1

Can the (in)famous anything series generate literally anything? No. They can't generate anything apart from anime styles.

So here you go. An ambitious model that can generate literally anything; from anime style to photorealistic "atashi".

items.name: Clothing: Star Trek Uniforms
items.description:
LORA for Star Trek uniforms. It responds to colors (so you can get red, blue, yellow, or any other color) but since it was trained on a variety of uniforms sometimes we will get a combination previously not seen in the shows/movies.

You can put colors in the prompt as well as in the negatives.

Tested on various models, also works on anime (although I'm bad with anime generations, someone could try to play with it and show us nicer results :P)

The trigger is strtrk uniform and it works well in someone wearing a strtrk uniform but other usages seem to work fine too.

As per usual, you can decrease or increase the LORA's strength. When I was playing with it I noticed that different models may want higher values than others (it also depends if you are mixing LORAs together).

But for typical generations, I was using strength between 1.1 and 1.35

If you want to see more examples, here is an Imgur gallery: https://imgur.com/a/7whYoPE

items.name: Makoto Shinkai (Your Name + substyles) Style LoRA
items.description:
Makoto Shinkai style LoRA

Includes substyles for Your Name, Weathering With You and The Garden of Words.

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕

Requested on Discord, this was trained on my hand selected and tagged dataset of anime screencaps. Trigger word is shinkai makoto and contains substyles that are each triggered with kimi no na wa. (mind the dot), tenki no ko, and kotonoha no niwa respectively. See the example images and final comparison. Keep in mind this is not a character lora. While it obviously overfitted on the main cast, it won't get characters accurately 100% of the time without a character specific LoRA/TI.

It works most accurately on AnyLoRA and I've offset it so that it works at 1 weight. Should actually work on most anime models and on NeverEnding Dream.

Clip skip 2 should be better, but careful as some of the examples are using Clip skip 1 because I forgot the setting from another test I was making. Pic 3 and 10 are generated with clip skip 1 and upscaled with clip skip 2.


How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight according to the instructions (by default it's :1)

items.name: Devin Brugman
items.description:
Devin Brugman is an American model and social media celebrity with more than 1M followers in Instagram.

Update: Retrained once again from scratch for 140 steps (ended up selectin step 135), I pruned my dataset, leaving it at a total of 15 images after discarding and replacing some pics.

Devin's was my 2nd TI here at CivitAI, if I recall correctly, and it was about time to update it. She's one of my favorite models and I've always wanted to make her justice with a good embedding. In fact, Devin was the fist subject I ever tried to make an embedding of, back in January this year... The attempt was such a disaster that I stopped trying for about a month. If you want to have a good laugh, here are the training images the AI generated while learning Dev's physique. The best part is I let it run up until step 4000. I probably was expecting it to improve at some point :_D. (By the way, the attempt was so bad for 2 main reasons: first, because I used Protogen as the training model instead of standard SD, and second because I used a 512x768 format. Rookie mistakes. ^^)

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (jg_dev1nbr:0.99), a woman with beautiful hair, hair upsweep updo, as a movie star in a (movie premiere), premiere gala, (near a movie theatre), natural skin texture, (elegant denim overalls), (long sleeve shirt), (suspenders:1.2), 24mm, 4k textures, soft cinematic light, adobe lightroom, photolab, hdr, intricate, elegant, highly detailed, sharp focus, ((((cinematic look)))), soothing tones, insane details, intricate details, hyperdetailed, low contrast, soft cinematic light, exposure blend, hdr, faded, (paparazzi in background), (painted lips:1.1), ((looking straight at the camera:1.1)), (hoop earrings)"

items.description:
Sweep Tosho (Umamusume) LoRA

This is the second LoRA I made, with one character supporting 3 outfits. Including racing uniform, school uniform and casual wear. Weight 0.8~1 will do well.

Please use this with respect for the original content, DO NOT publish any NSFW content.

I am using new training parameter, size is much smaller and retaining somewhat similar quality and style, enjoy!

Recommended prompt:

For more accurate result, please use the following prompt for each outfit

Racing outfit

sweep tosho \(umamusume\), shobufuku, witch hat, twintails, hair rings,  very long hair, black robe, white gloves, wide sleeves, white skirt, thigh boots

School Uniform

sweep tosho \(umamusume\), natsufuku, witch hat, very long hair, twintails, hair rings, pleated skirt, puffy short sleeves, purple bow, white skirt, sailor collar, sailor shirt, tracen school uniform, white thighhighs, brown footwear

Casual Wear

sweep tosho \(umamusume\), fudangi, hair bow, red bow, red dress, long sleeves, short necktie, very long hair, twintails, hair rings, white kneehighs, black footwear

*It is possible to switch between “witch hat” and “hair bow” to take on/off her headwear

**Use "thigh boots", "thighhighs", "footwear" only while drawing lower body or full body, or it will force AI to draw in full body scale.

***Use "from behind", "v-shaped eyebrows:1.5" in negative prompt may help

Known problem

For unknown reason school uniform may mix with racing outfit sometimes, add "shobufuku" in negative prompt if necessary.

For unknown reason eyebrows are constantly v-shaped, add "v-shaped eyebrows:1.5" in negative prompt may help her looks more relaxed.

Adding "horse tail" will generate tail but dont expect on right place.

Again, Please use this with respect for the original content, DO NOT publish any NSFW content.

Note: I may update my Special Week model to a smaller sized one if I have time.

(Oh she looks a bit older than her age? No way, THATs my taste lol)

With a lot of attitude, Chantel knows she is a baddie even though she has the whole black Barbie doll look going on. items.name: Curren Chan (umamusume)
items.description:
LoRA of Curren Chan (umamusume)

All of my works is free. If you'd like to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee. 👍

Recommend options

  • LoRA weight 0.6~1.0

  • Trigger words

    • base

      • curren chan \(umamusume\)

      • (optional)smile, hands on own chin,

    • Racing competition clothes :

      • vertical-striped dress, bare shoulders, off shoulder, closed mouth, long sleeves, collared dress, gloves

    • Wedding costume :

      • elbow gloves, black wedding dress, black gloves, string of fate, official alternate costume, closed mouth, bare shoulders, sleeveless dress

    • Casual clothes :

      • jewelry, white shirt, white long sleeves, necklace, red skirt, sleeves past wrists, black pantyhose

        • maybe white shirt need more weight

  • Use animefull based model

  • Settings

    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • about 20 steps, CFG scale 3.5~6.5

    • kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

    • If using highres

      • Latent series

      • Denoising strength 0.50~0.65

LoRA training info

  • based on Animefull-pruned

  • 133 images of curren chan

    • 4x low quality 42 images

    • 8x medium quality 48 images

    • 16x high quality 43 images

    • => 1 epoch = 1240 images

  • replaced character feature tags with curren chan \(umamusume\)

    • horse girl, horse tail, pink hair, purple eyes, etc.

  • using aspect ratio bucketing

  • resolution : 768x768

  • rank=alpha=16

  • using dadaptation

  • batch size = 4, 9 epochs trained

  • clip skip = 1

This LoRA may be compatible with animefull-based models (ex. AbyssOrangeMix Series...)

All uploaded images are generated by AOM3A1

items.name: Elyse Willems LoRA
items.description:
This is a LoRa model of Elyse Willems, trained on 17 high quality images with accurate captions.

The training was done with the kohya LoRA model, so it requires the LoRa extension for Automatic1111 to function.


The model was trained against RealisticVision 1.3 but produces good results with artEros, hasdX and uberrealisticDreamy as well.

I would recommend a CFG scale of 7, LoRA weight of 0.9 or 1 and 35-45 steps, I had the best results with that.

The triggerword is loraelyse, I would recommend using similar wording to the prompts in the examples, at least for the positive prompt.

items.name: 3d Girls (Lora) [2b d.va widowmaker ]
items.description:
Trained on wild's mix

OVER 7000 IMGS! 60+ CHARACTERS

PROMPTING

Use With vae-ft-mse-840000!

Positive Prompt:

  • Masterpiece, 3d,

Example:

  • Masterpiece, 3d, 1girl, akali,

When training the Lora network the Masterpiece keyword was added to the best images so when used in prompt it improves image quality.

Negative Prompt:

  • lowres, ugly, tiling, poorly drawn hands, poorly drawn feet, poorly drawn face, out of frame, extra limbs, disfigured, deformed, body out of frame, bad anatomy, watermark, grainy, signature, cut off

Notice the prompt doesn't have the the word blurred or blurry since most of the images were 3D and have a blurry Depth Of Field it generally is better though not required to remove blurry from the negative prompt.

This was trained to be a general 3d network as a result there are alot of characters in the LORA.

items.name: The Ally's Mix III: Revolutions
items.description:
Please consider joining my Patreon! Advanced SD tutorials, explanations, exclusive embeddings, adult-art, from a female content creator (me!) patreon.com/theally

A THIRD version?!

Yup! But my first NSFW 🔞 focused release. Sure, it does good SFW portraits, and other content, but it excels at the naughty stuff. It also contains the amazing Noise Offset code/process, so it produces EXCELLENT darkness - true darkness, which hasn't really been consistently possible until now. Lots of great contrast, deep shadows, etc. It's very grim and moody.

What's in it?

I've taken my Ally's Mix II: Churned, cut in a dash of my favourite model, ReV Animated, then taken the result of that + Noise Offset - SD 1.5.

STOP AND READ, LoRA FANS!

This is mixed with the OG Noise Offset model by Nicholas Guttenberg at Crosslabs

You cannot - CANNOT - extract a LoRA from this model and get similar results to the model. The noise offset does not extract. You have to train the noise offset in, or cut it in with a difference merge.

If you extract this model to LoRA, it will look like shit, and kids will point and laugh at you in the street.

I am making a LoRA from this model, the correct way, ty 💗

Recreating my sample images?!

Some of my sample images are created with ControlNet, to get poses and compositions from my previous generations - you'll never be able to reproduce those. Others, it's possible, but some do use Patron exclusive embeddings. The sample images are meant to show what's possible with a model. I do have a tutorial on Patreon on recreating my images, the common settings I use, etc.
